National Grid Names Peter Gershon as Chairman to Succeed Parker

-- B y   B r i a n   S w i n t
-- 
2011-07-01T08:48:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/national-grid-names-peter-gershon-as-chairman-to-succeed-parker.html
National Grid Plc (NG/) , operator of
Britain’s power-distribution network, appointed Peter Gershon as
chairman from Jan. 1 to succeed John Parker.  Gershon, 64, is also the chairman of food ingredients maker
Tate & Lyle Plc and left the board of  Premier Farnell Plc (PFL)  last
month. He was responsible for GEC Plc’s defense business from
1994 to 1999, before the unit was sold to BAE Systems Plc.  An engineer by training, he led a review of the efficiency
of the U.K. public sector in 2003 at the request of then-Prime
Minister  Tony Blair . He was knighted in 2004.  Gershon will join the board of National Grid on Aug. 1 as
deputy chairman until Parker steps down at the start of 2012,
the company said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Swint in London at 
